task.summary: Edited main layout to reflect the proper appearance of the navigation utility's single destination input. Working on getting the origin and destination from their respective input fields so I can then send them to the google service and receive back the map data. After that will be the task of building the map and displaying it.
Updated the look of the navigation utility. Looks more fluid and less bulky now.

Created an observer subject relationship for the enabling and disabling of the navigate me button, pending that both location inputs (origin and destination) are not empty. The observer will update the button, and the subject will wrap each EditText, enabling them to notify their observer when they are empty or not empty.
Navigate me button is now only enabled if both text fields contain no less than one character.

Had to make many project file changes tonight, lots of time eaten as a result. Created a view in which to display the navigation map, as well as a class to handle its initial state and future actions performed on it.
Map is now fully displayed and centers on the user's current location from the beginning. It will update whenever the user's location changes.
